tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria and tubular dysfunction. The presence of glucose and ketones in urine with low HbA1c and normal blood glucose is unusual and may indicate a non-diabetic cause. Urine is cloudy and brown, but no evidence of infection. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended to clarify the underlying renal pathology.
